'''Fcitx''' ('''F'''ree '''C'''hinese '''I'''nput '''T'''oy for '''X''') <nowiki>[ˈfaɪtɪks]</nowiki> is an input method framework with extension support.

== Installation ==
Install {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx}}:
{{USEflag|package=app-i18n/fcitx
|cairo+yes+yes
|debug
|gtk++yes+Install GTK2 IM module
|gtk3+++Install GTK3 IM module
|introspection
|lua
|opencc
|pango+yes+yes
|qt4++yes
|snooper
|static-libs
|table+yes++Adds support for table-based IM systems like Wubi, Erbi
}}
{{Note|It is strongly recommended to add the ''gtk'', ''gtk3'' and ''qt4'' USE flags when you have applications using these toolkits.}}

{{Emerge|app-i18n/fcitx}}

== Using Fcitx ==
In order to use Fcitx in X, you need to add these environment variables (you need to export them after setting these variables):

If you use GDM, KDM or [[LightDM]] to login, add them to {{Path|~/.xprofile}}. If you use '''startx''', SLiM, etc. to login, add them to {{Path|~/.xinitrc}}.

<pre>
XIM=fcitx
XIM_PROGRAM=fcitx
XMODIFIERS="@im=fcitx"
QT_IM_MODULE=<module>
GTK_IM_MODULE=<module>
</pre>

If you add gtk, gtk3 and qt4 to <code>USE</code>, &lt;module&gt; will be `fcitx', otherwise it should be `xim'.

It is recommended to start the [[D-Bus]] session bus before Fcitx starts.
Add these to the '''beginning''' of your X startup file ({{Path|~/.xprofile}} or {{Path|~/.xinitrc}}):
<pre>
eval "$(dbus-launch --sh-syntax --exit-with-session)"
</pre>

{{Warning|If you want to use Fcitx in X, your [[Localization|locale]] '''cannot''' be ''C'' or ''POSIX''.}}

== Configuration ==
You can edit Fcitx's configuration file at {{Path|~/.config/fcitx/config}}.

Also, there is a tool to configure Fcitx called {{Package|app-i18n/fcitx-configtool}} (You may need to add the '~arch' keyword in {{Path|package.accept_keywords}} to install it).

